cs.LG, cs.OM, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper describes a modeling framework that integrates predictive modeling and prescriptive analysis, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.OM (Operations Research), which deals with optimization problems. The paper also discusses the use of linear regression, logistic regression, and neural networks, which are common in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on business research practice, which falls under the sub-category of computational economics (cs.CE). Finally, the paper involves the integration of different streams of analytics, which could also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
